<dd>A word describing the feeling of pungency at the tip of the tongue, nose, etc.</dd><br>
<dt>쫄랑쫄랑 [쫄랑쫄랑]</dt><br>
<dd>1. gently</dd><br>
<dd>물 등이 자꾸 작은 물결을 이루며 흔들리는 소리. 또는 그 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word used to describe the shaking sound made when water, etc., forms small ripples, or such a motion.</dd><br>
<dd>2. playfully</dd><br>
<dd>자꾸 가볍고 조심성 없게 까부는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of acting lightly and playfully with no regard to caution.</dd><br>
<dt>지그시 [지그시]</dt><br>
<dd>1. softly; gently</dd><br>
<dd>슬며시 힘을 주는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of applying pressure lightly.</dd><br>
<dd>2. patiently</dd><br>
<dd>조용히 참고 견디는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of enduring quietly.</dd><br>
<dt>졸졸 [졸졸]</dt><br>
<dd>1. continuously; gently</dd><br>
<dd>가는 물줄기 등이 계속해서 부드럽게 흐르는 소리. 또는 그런 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>With a sound resembling the one that is produced when a thin, narrow flow of water, etc., keeps running gently, or such an action.</dd><br>
<dd>2. continuously</dd><br>
<dd>작은 동물이나 사람이 자꾸 뒤를 따라다니는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In such a manner that occurs when a small animal or human keeps following another around.</dd><br>
<dd>3. all over the place</dd><br>
<dd>작은 물건을 여기저기 자꾸 흘리는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In such a manner that one keeps spilling small objects here and there.</dd><br>
<dd>4. without stopping</dd><br>
<dd>조금도 막힘이 없이 글을 읽거나 쓰거나 말하는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In such a manner that one reads, writes or speaks without faltering a bit.</dd><br>
<dt>졸랑졸랑 [졸랑졸랑]</dt><br>
<dd>1. gently</dd><br>
<dd>물 등이 자꾸 작은 물결을 이루며 흔들리는 소리. 또는 그 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In a manner of water, etc., forming small ripples repeatedly and producing shaking sound, or such a shape.</dd><br>
<dd>2. playfully</dd><br>
<dd>자꾸 가볍고 조심성 없게 까부는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In a manner of acting lightly and playfully with no regard to caution.</dd><br>
<dt>조르르 [조르르]</dt><br>
<dd>1. gently</dd><br>
<dd>가는 물줄기 등이 빠르게 흘러내리는 소리. 또는 그 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In such a manner that a thin, narrow flow of water, etc., runs down, or the sound made by such a flow.</dd><br>
<dd>2. quickly</dd><br>
<dd>작은 사람이나 물건 등이 기울어진 곳에서 빠르게 미끄러져 내리는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In such a manner that a small person, object, etc., quickly slides down a slope.</dd><br>
<dd>3. quickly</dd><br>
<dd>작고 재빠른 걸음으로 걷거나 따라다니는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In a manner of walking or following someone in small quick steps.</dd><br>
<dd>4. neatly</dd><br>
<dd>작은 것들이 한 줄로 고르게 있는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In a manner of a group of small objects being in a single, neat file.</dd><br>
<dt>조록조록 [조록쪼록]</dt><br>
<dd>gently; softly</dd><br>
<dd>비나 가는 물줄기 등이 빠르게 자꾸 내리거나 흐르는 소리 또는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>With a sound resembling one that is produced when rain or a narrow stream of water falls down quickly and continuously, or such an action.</dd><br>
<dt>잔잔히 [잔잔히]</dt><br>
<dd>1. calmly; tranquilly; quietly</dd><br>
<dd>바람이나 물결 등이 심하지 않고 움직임이 거의 없이.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of the wind, a wave, etc., being still and not severe.</dd><br>
<dd>2. serenely; tranquilly; calmly</dd><br>
<dd>분위기가 고요하고 평화롭게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of an atmosphere being silent and peaceful.</dd><br>
<dd>3. calmly; serenely</dd><br>
<dd>표정이나 태도 등이 차분하고 평온하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of one's look, attitude, etc., being composed and peaceful.</dd><br>
<dd>4. gently</dd><br>
<dd>소리가 조용하고 부드럽게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of a sound being quiet and soft.</dd><br>
<dt>원만히 [원만히]</dt><br>
<dd>1. mildly; gently</dd><br>
<dd>성격이 부드럽고 너그럽게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of one's personality being gentle and generous.</dd><br>
<dd>2. smoothly; peacefully</dd><br>
<dd>일의 진행이 순조롭게.</dd><br>
<dd>In a state in which the progress of something is smooth.</dd><br>
<dd>3. intimately; harmoniously</dd><br>
<dd>서로 사이가 좋게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of getting along well with each other.</dd><br>
<dt>얌전히 [얌전히]</dt><br>
<dd>1. gently; meekly</dd><br>
<dd>성격이나 태도가 조용하고 차분하게.</dd><br>
<dd>With a quiet and calm personality or attitude.</dd><br>
<dd>2. neatly; cleanly; tidily</dd><br>
<dd>모양이 단정하고 반듯하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In a neat and tidy shape.</dd><br>
<dt>슬슬 [슬슬]</dt><br>
<dd>1. stealthily</dd><br>
<dd>남이 알아차리지 못하게 천천히 조용하게 행동하는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of acting slowly and quietly so that others do not know.</dd><br>
<dd>2. imperceptibly; softly</dd><br>
<dd>눈이나 설탕 등이 모르는 사이에 저절로 녹는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing snow, sugar, etc., melting away before one knows.</dd><br>
<dd>3. softly; gently</dd><br>
<dd>세지 않게 만지거나 문지르는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of touching or rubbing something tenderly.</dd><br>
<dd>4. adroitly; gently</dd><br>
<dd>겉으로 드러나지 않게 은근히 설득하는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of persuading someone indirectly so that one's intention is not revealed.</dd><br>
<dd>5. gently</dd><br>
<dd>바람이 가볍고 부드럽게 부는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing the wind blowing lightly and softly.</dd><br>
<dd>6. gently</dd><br>
<dd>가볍게 눈웃음을 치는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of smiling with one's eyes lightly.</dd><br>
<dd>7. slowly</dd><br>
<dd>서두르지 않고 천천히 행동하는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of acting slowly, not hastening.</dd><br>
<dd>8. effortlessly</dd><br>
<dd>힘들이지 않고 쉽게 하는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of doing something easily without much effort.</dd><br>
<dt>슬며시 [슬며시]</dt><br>
<dd>1. gently</dd><br>
<dd>남이 알아차리지 못하도록 드러나지 않게 가만히.</dd><br>
<dd>In a gentle manner that someone behaves so that other people will not notice.</dd><br>
<dd>2. lightly</dd><br>
<dd>행동이나 상황이 뚜렷하게 드러나지 않고 천천히.</dd><br>
<dd>In a slow manner that an action or situation is not exposed clearly.</dd><br>
<dd>3. slowly</dd><br>
<dd>속으로 천천히 은밀하게.</dd><br>
<dd>In a manner of being slow and secretive.</dd><br>
<dt>술술 [술술]</dt><br>
<dd>1. smoothly</dd><br>
<dd>물이나 가루 등이 틈이나 구멍으로 잇따라 조금씩 새어 나오는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing water, powder, etc., coming through a crack or hole little by little.</dd><br>
<dd>2. gently</dd><br>
<dd>바람이 부드럽게 부는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing the wind blowing softly.</dd><br>
<dd>3. lightly</dd><br>
<dd>가는 비나 눈이 잇따라 가볍게 내리는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing a fine rain or snow falling lightly.</dd><br>
<dd>4. fluently; smoothly</dd><br>
<dd>말이나 글이 막힘없이 잘 나오거나 써지는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of speaking or writing without hesitation.</dd><br>
<dd>5. smoothly</dd><br>
<dd>묶이거나 엉킨 실이나 끈이 쉽게 잘 풀리는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing a tangled or bound thread or string disentangling easily.</dd><br>
<dd>6. easily</dd><br>
<dd>해결하기 어려운 일이나 문제가 쉽게 풀리는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of a knotty or difficult problem being solved easily.</dd><br>
<dt>솔솔 [솔솔]</dt><br>
<dd>1. smoothly</dd><br>
<dd>물이나 가루 등이 틈이나 구멍으로 조금씩 새어 나오는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing water, powder, etc., coming through a crack or hole little by little.</dd><br>
<dd>2. gently</dd><br>
<dd>바람이 부드럽게 부는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing the wind blowing softly.</dd><br>
<dd>3. lightly</dd><br>
<dd>가는 비나 눈이 잇따라 가볍게 내리는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing a fine rain or snow falling lightly.</dd><br>
<dd>4. fluently; smoothly</dd><br>
<dd>말이나 글이 막힘없이 잘 나오거나 써지는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of speaking or writing without hesitation.</dd><br>
<dd>5. smoothly</dd><br>
<dd>묶이거나 엉킨 실이나 끈이 쉽게 잘 풀리는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>A word describing a tangled or bound thread or string disentangling easily.</dd><br>
<dd>6. easily</dd><br>
<dd>해결하기 어려운 일이나 문제가 쉽게 풀리는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of a knotty or difficult problem being solved easily.</dd><br>
<dd>7. lightly</dd><br>
<dd>가볍게 냄새가 나거나 연기가 피어오르는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of a smell or smoke rising lightly.</dd><br>
<dd>8. quietly</dd><br>
<dd>재미가 은근히 나는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of feeling interested quietly.</dd><br>
<dd>9. slowly; quietly</dd><br>
<dd>잠에 조금씩 빠지는 모양.</dd><br>
<dd>In the state of falling asleep slowly.</dd><br>
<dt>소르르 [소르르]</dt><br>
<dd>1. smoothly; readily</dd><br>
